#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:8
msgid "# Galactic Space Pirates"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:10
msgid "The Galactic Space Pirates are split into two main groups, the clans and independent pirates."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:11
msgid "Among the independent pirates are marauders who are extremely aggressive and not very well-equipped."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:12
msgid "Other pirates tend to be better equipped and usually strive to join one of the major pirate clans."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:14
msgid "The four main clans are the <%= strblacklotus %>, <%= strwildones %>, <%= strravenclan %>, and <%= strdreamerclan %>."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:16
msgid "## Organization"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:18
msgid "* **Leader:** Pirate Lords from the diverse clans"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:19
msgid "* **Leading Structure:** Pirate Assembly"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:20
msgid "* **Government:** Aristocracy (varies by clan)"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:21
msgid "* **Formation:** Beginning of History"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:22
msgid "* **Homeworld:** Varies by Clan"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:24
msgid "## Independent Pirates"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:26
msgid "Formed by individuals that have given up on society and turned to piracy to make a living."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:27
msgid "They form a large part of all pirates and end up doing lots of the grunt work for the clans."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:28
msgid "As long as they do not cause problems they are welcome at all pirate clansworlds."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:30
msgid "## Marauders"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:32
msgid "Usually formed by individuals that are not fit by the clans due to extreme violence, no critical thinking, problematic behaviour, no hygiene, or all of the above."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:33
msgid "They are tolerated by other pirates, who tend to exploit them and give them scraps, but they usually end up with short life spans."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:35
msgid "## Pirate Assemblies"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:37
msgid "Usually occurring once a cycle, pirate assemblies are as formal of a gathering as you can find in the pirate world."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:38
msgid "They are usually held at a more neutral pirate clansworld, such as those of the <%= strravenclan %>, and consist of several [decaperiods](mechanics/time) of partying and lawmaking."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:39
msgid "The main event consists of the meeting of the Pirate Lords who will listen to proposals and decide on courses of actions, while letting their crew loose."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:41
msgid "The assemblies tend to be a good opportunity for the Pirate Lords to calculate each other strengths, where they tend to bring significant ships from their fleet."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:42
msgid "In many ways, the pirate assemblies tend to not only determine the future of the space pirates, but also tend to shape the future of the galaxy."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:44
msgid "The events tend to also attract the attention of other actors in the galaxy, with most Great Houses and [the Empire](lore/factions/empire) sending somewhat undercover agents to try to get a glimpse of what is going on and gain advantage over other Great Houses."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:45
msgid "It is also common for less scrupulous merchants to show up as it can be a very profitable opportunity to sell grog and equipment to the drunken pirates."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:48
msgid "## Wild Ones Clan"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:50
msgid "Formed mainly by [Empire](lore/factions/empire) and [Soromid](lore/factions/soromid) outcasts, the Wild Ones are a violent and aggressive clan where strength is of utmost importance."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:51
msgid "Weaker individuals tend to follow the stronger ones, and the strongest compete against each other."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:52
msgid "That said, there are few deadly confrontations between clan members, as usually the weaker one will back out and submit when they see they don't have a chance."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:53
msgid "They tend to not hold grudges, which allows for their society to work."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:55
msgid "The clan's territory is the sparsely inhabited area between the [Empire](lore/factions/empire) and the [Soromid](lore/factions/soromid)."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:56
msgid "Their main clansworld was Haven, until it was destroyed in an offensive by the Empire and Great Houses."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:57
msgid "Since then, they have moved to a more secluded area known as New Haven where they are careful to not repeat the same fate."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:59
msgid "Although they get along well with the <%= strravenclan %>, they tend to get into fights with the <%= strblacklotus %>, and look down upon the <%= strdreamerclan %>."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:63
msgid "## Raven Clan"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:65
msgid "Arguably the clan that connects all the pirates and maintains the infrastructure for their success."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:66
msgid "The Raven Clan is formed by many ex-merchants who were fed up with the corruption and bureaucracy of the Imperial system, and decided to do their own thing."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:67
msgid "Although they deal in smuggling and black-market trade, they do not shun nor turn away from the occasional raid or assassination."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:68
msgid "They are very diplomatic and put strong emphasis on human relationships, which they foster to maximize the success of their trading endeavours."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:70
msgid "The Raven Clan mainly inhabits the Qorel tunnel, which is a chain of systems not accessible through standard jump points."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:71
msgid "They have several bases along it and use their cunning and secrecy to supply goods and connect all the pirates together."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:72
msgid "Due to their fundamental role, they tend to have strong connections and relationships with all the other pirate clans."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:73
msgid "They also work with corrupt officials of the Great Houses, and pretty much anyone that has the credits to pay."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:77
msgid "## Black Lotus"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:79
msgid "One of the most well organized pirate clans, the Black Lotus prides itself in methodology and organization."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:80
msgid "Members follow strict recruitment policies to slowly go up in the ranks and gain more power in the hierarchy, very similar to large corporations."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:81
msgid "Discipline is swift and punishment is carried out in public form to make sure everyone follows the rules, making them one of the most rigid pirate clans."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:83
msgid "They inhabit the pocket of space between [House Za'lek](lore/factions/zalek) and [House Dvaered](lore/factions/dvaered), where they make a fortune from specializing in stolen research equipment and oddities from the universe."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:84
msgid "They also tend to run protection rackets, which are often favoured over the whimsical [Dvaered](lore/factions/dvaered) Warlords and can provide more stability to the area."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:85
msgid "While the price of these protection contracts is quite high, wealthy citizens have found that they are well worth the money, as any failed protection contract is met with swift discipline for those who failed, making failure rates extremely low."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:89
msgid "## Dreamer Clan"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:91
msgid "The newest of the main pirate clans, the Dreamer Clan was able to capitalize on [the Incident](lore/history/incident) and establish itself as a force to be reckoned with."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:92
msgid "Formed mainly by refugees and outcasts of the so-called \"civilized society\", the Dreamer Clan is formed by individuals who do not want to follow rules."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:93
msgid "They have no hierarchy and form an eclectic and anarchistic bunch, giving lots of leeway for personal freedom and using voting and other systems to decide how to take action."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:94
msgid "Although they rely heavily on piracy, most individuals pursue artistic talents when not raiding nearby convoys or scavenging from wrecks from [the Incident](lore/history/incident)."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:95
msgid "They are also renowned for being a large hub of illicit substances, which their members use freely and some claim to get Sirius-like psychic powers from substance abuse."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:97
msgid "They are located in the Nebula, near [House Sirius](lore/factions/sirius) and [the Frontier](lore/factions/frontier), making use of abandoned planets and stations, which they adapt to their purposes."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:98
msgid "Although they tend to have little contact with other pirates outside of assemblies, they have lots of trade with the <%= strravenclan %>, which wants access to the lucrative drug trade."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/pirates.md:99
msgid "Although in general less organized than other clans, they can be ruthless at raiding convoys, sometimes going deep into [House Sirius](lore/factions/sirius) space."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:2
msgid "Sovereign Proteron Autarchy"
msgstr ""


#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:6
msgid "<widget wgtfct />"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:8
msgid "# Sovereign Proteron Autarchy"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:10
msgid "Formed from the former Great House Proteron, the Sovereign Proteron Autarchy played a pivotal role in the history of the universe."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:11
msgid "It arose from an Emperor's desire to create a revolution in the sphere of society and societal structure."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:12
msgid "The project performed all too well, creating a Great House that surpassed its progenitor in nearly every way, and chafing at its restraints."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:13
msgid "These tensions escalated into all-out war, with devastating consequences for both bodies, because neither have the Proteron heard of restraint nor the Emperor of caution."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:15
msgid "## Oganization"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:17
msgid "* **Leader:** High Autarch Python"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:18
msgid "* **Leading Structure:** Circle of Autarchs"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:19
msgid "* **Government:** Autarchy"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:20
msgid "* **Formation:** UST 47"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:21
msgid "* **Homeworld:** ??? <!-- TODO: find the actual homeworld -->"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:23
msgid "## House Proteron Society"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:25
msgid "House Proteron worlds were governed by a totalitarian regime that required its citizens to follow their dictated daily routines, severely punishing transgressions under a zero-tolerance policy."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:26
msgid "A Proteron citizen was never their own person."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:27
msgid "They were an asset of the government, their life's labour neatly represented in a bookkeeping column somewhere."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:28
msgid "Even the details of their private life were managed and tallied by the authorities."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:29
msgid "Despite the lack of freedom and privacy, Proteron citizens were not slaves."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:30
msgid "The government kept them in top shape, providing an adequate supply of health care, relaxation, and entertainment, making sure all predispositions and tastes were catered for."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:31
msgid "This kept citizens happy to trade independence and privacy for comfort and security."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:32
msgid "As such, a subject was often able and willing to work at optimal performance."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:33
msgid "A Proteron citizen's life was thus quite a satisfying one, though excitement other than the terminal kind was rare."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:35
msgid "House Proteron's worlds were all specialist worlds."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:36
msgid "They were geared to performing a limited selection of tasks according to the planet's natural properties or location."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:37
msgid "The inhabitants on a world were placed there by the government."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:38
msgid "Each individual was measured and tested, then sent to the world where they could be of the most use."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:39
msgid "As such, Proteron society was built of individuals rather than families - a family would only have complicated the relocation process."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:41
msgid "The local planetary governments were directly responsible to an Autarch."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:42
msgid "An Autarch managed many worlds as a sector, with the number depending on how densely populated and productive the worlds were."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:43
msgid "Once every four cycles all the Proteron Autarchs met in a Circle."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:44
msgid "During these meeting, the Autarchs would evaluate the development of each Proteron world individually as well as that of the greater Proteron body in general."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:45
msgid "Based on this evaluation, goals were set for the next four cycles."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:46
msgid "Each Autarch was expected to meet or exceed these goals, and those Autarchs who failed to do so were removed from office - in a very permanent manner."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:48
msgid "For period-to-period and urgent decisions that could not wait for many cycles, and further to ensure that the Circle did not become complacent, the Proteron also had a High Autarch."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:49
msgid "They and the Circle were supposed to balance each other's power."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:51
msgid "## History"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:53
msgid "When [the Empire](lore/factions/empire) was still the undisputed power in the galaxy, it knew it could not last unless it was prepared to change with the times."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:54
msgid "As the people lived, adapted and expanded through the universe, there would undoubtedly be problems that could not be addressed by an antiquated regime."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:55
msgid "A repetition of the Faction Wars was to be avoided at all costs."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:56
msgid "Therefore, [the Empire](lore/factions/empire) set up Project Proteron, an experimental environment to test new forms of government and galactic administration."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:57
msgid "The purpose of Project Proteron was to be the test-bed of the \"next generation\" Empire, an improved form of government that would keep the galaxy stable and under the rule of the Emperor."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:59
msgid "Project Proteron was limited to a few worlds at first, on the basis that a galactic government could only succeed given stable planetary governments."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:60
msgid "Soon, however, the scope of the project expanded as its overseers came to the conclusion that planetary government needed to be designed simultaneously with galaxy-wide administration."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:61
msgid "Within a decacycle of its inception, the worlds assigned to Project Proteron numbered more than a dozen."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:63
msgid "[The Empire](lore/factions/empire), eager to see results, continued to push the experiment to work faster and more efficiently."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:64
msgid "As a direct result of this, the more liberal, decentralized processes were eliminated from the test roster, and more emphasis was put on controlled, high-yield social structures."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:65
msgid "More and more planets were added to the project, its populations relocated, re-educated and re-assigned for a better turnout."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:66
msgid "The concepts of personal liberties and privacy became more and more secondary to the collective performance, and eventually were abandoned altogether by those who led the Project."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:68
msgid "The expansion and results of the Project led the Emperor to promote Project Proteron from an Empire-commissioned Project to a fully-fledged, independent Great House."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:69
msgid "The philosophy was that House Proteron would eventually become a prototype for the New Empire, and once all the bugs were ironed out, its model would be implemented in the entire known galaxy and House Proteron would once again be part of the greater Empire."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:71
msgid "### The Sovereign Proteron Autarchy and the Incident"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:73
msgid "With its new title, House Proteron enjoyed more freedom and independence than it had so far, ironically."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:74
msgid "Its leaders eagerly made use of their increased authority, further fine-tuning House Proteron for economic and industrial efficiency as well as social control."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:75
msgid "Taxes were levied."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:76
msgid "Ships were built."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:77
msgid "A well-oiled military machine and intelligence agency were created from scratch, securing House Proteron from hostile influences from within and without."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:78
msgid "In only a few decacycles, House Proteron had become a powerful diplomatic and economic factor in the galaxy."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:80
msgid "As time passed, House Proteron began to notice the cracks in the old Empire."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:81
msgid "Already unhappy with the Emperor's reticence in dealing decisively with the Sirii, [the Empire](lore/factions/empire)'s handling of the Dvaered disgusted the Proteron."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:82
msgid "Rather than reassigning the workers and improving their living standards to allow them to reach their true potential, [the Empire](lore/factions/empire) gave up on them."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:83
msgid "In addition, it had been centacycles since the Za'lek had given more than the cursory nod to Imperial authority."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:84
msgid "The Proteron generally blamed [the Empire](lore/factions/empire)'s social structure for its inability to command the loyalty of its subjects."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:85
msgid "Their House, on the other hand, had grown by leaps and bounds, claiming more and more space for their systems, even bordering Sol."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:86
msgid "The final straw was the Quarantine of Sorom, where [the Empire](lore/factions/empire) simply laid down and let a disease claim a whole planet."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:88
msgid "Some debate followed, but the consensus was that House Proteron had achieved its original goal, and now it was time for the weak Empire to make way for the new generation of galactic dominance."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:89
msgid "But when the Proteron High Autarch delivered this message to the Emperor, he was furious at the perceived insult and ordered all Autarchs executed."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:90
msgid "Appalled at this reaction, the Circle concluded in an emergency meeting that [the Empire](lore/factions/empire) had no intention of honouring the original agreement, thereby forfeiting its claim to the loyalty of House Proteron."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:91
msgid "It was clear to the Circle that should [the Empire](lore/factions/empire) insist on trying to turn the Proteron into another Dvaered incident or, worse still, turning them into Empire systems, there could be no peace with them."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:93
msgid "Knowing that they could not resist the entire might of [the Empire](lore/factions/empire)'s infrastructure, the Proteron decided to plant their agents in every major Imperial agency while publicly grovelling at [the Empire](lore/factions/empire)'s feet."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:94
msgid "Soon enough, the Proteron were even in charge of [the Empire](lore/factions/empire)'s covert operations against the Proteron."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:95
msgid "Now having loosened their leash greatly, they set out to prepare for a galaxy-scale war."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:96
msgid "While they worked, however, the shape of the galaxy was changing."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:98
msgid "New advances in quantum engineering led to the development of quantum transtators and translators."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:99
msgid "Alternative travel engines were developed that were capable of bypassing warp points, challenging conventional military doctrine which recommended fortifying choke point systems on the warp network."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:100
msgid "Expecting correctly that [the Empire](lore/factions/empire) had not even thought of this change, the Proteron decided to bypass their defences using the new hypergate being built in Sol."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:101
msgid "After all, once the Emperor and their successors were in their hands, the war would be essentially meaningless."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:102
msgid "They built a hypergate in secret in their home system, Protera."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:103
msgid "They seceded from Imperial authority as soon as the gate was built and moved a small fleet as a feint into the classical defences."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:104
msgid "When [the Empire](lore/factions/empire) took the bait, the Sovereign Proteron Autarchy, as they now called themselves, sent the most massive fleet ever seen through their hypergate."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:106
msgid "Then [the Incident](lore/history/incident) occurred."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:108
msgid "After the dust settled, Protera was inaccessible, Sol was unreachable, their planets, factories and fleets had been decimated and the Circle was mostly gone."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:109
msgid "Thankfully, enough of the hierarchy remained that Proteron society did not dissolve."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:110
msgid "The Proteron scientists set out to determine the cause of [the Incident](lore/history/incident), and their best answer is that the large number of ships travelling all at once through the hypergate overloaded it, causing Sol to explode with a huge mass of material, causing a chain reaction that obliterated systems and changed the warp network."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:111
msgid "On the other hand, Protera was visible with no occlusion by the Nebula, but every scout they sent started to behave erratically and eventually stop communicating."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:112
msgid "Seeing this, the new Circle issued a moratorium on exploring the systems toward Protera."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:114
msgid "Armed with the knowledge of their situation and their error in the first attempt, the tenacious Sovereign Proteron Autarchy is continuing pursuit of its goal to take over [the Empire](lore/factions/empire)."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:115
msgid "They are already constructing an improved hypergate that will not fail like the last one did."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:117
msgid "## Proteron military tactics"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:119
msgid "The Proteron favour pilots on the larger spaceships and keep smaller ships unmanned."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:120
msgid "Extensive simulations, dogfights and mock battles revealed that fighters and bombers were largely outclassed by a fleet of unmanned drones, being harder to replace and less maneuverable."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:121
msgid "This means that their fleet strategy is not easily adjusted on the fly, so they developed the Euler, a fast and stealthy scout ship to ensure that there are no surprises facing the fleet when it commits to an attack."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:122
msgid "Similarly, it is illogical to commit before probing the enemy's weaknesses, so fleets consisting of smaller ships harass and draw out enemy fleets until the capital ships and their fleets of drones can reduce the enemy to dust."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:123
msgid "Proteron strategists understand a ship must be either capable of damage or of movement, else it is merely a sitting duck."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:124
msgid "Thus, their destroyers and corvettes are faster than expected for ships of their size."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:126
msgid "Further, the fleet does not believe that the pilot should hesitate to sacrifice themselves to help the fleet on the path to victory."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:127
msgid "As such, the Proteron largely follow a doctrine of no retreat to encourage pilots to fight to the death unless otherwise ordered."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/proteron.md:128
msgid "The larger ships with the pilots are therefore also built to outlast any enemy in damage-dealing capability."
msgstr ""

