msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:7
msgid "# Great House Sirius"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:9
msgid "The House Sirius is one of the Great Houses in [the Empire](lore/factions/empire)."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:11
msgid "## Organization"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:13
msgid "* **Leader:** Sirichana"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:14
msgid "* **Leading Structure:** Tribunal of Arch-Canters"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:15
msgid "* **Government:** Constitutional Theocracy"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:16
msgid "* **Formation:** [UST 97](lore/history)"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:17
msgid "* **Homeworld:** Mutris (Aesir system)"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:19
msgid "## Social Structure"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:21
msgid "House Sirius is defined by its state religion more than anything else."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:22
msgid "Its citizens all follow the same faith, and this faith is central to most of the goings-on in Sirius space."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:23
msgid "This is not to say every Sirius citizen is a religious fanatic; the Sirius have a healthy intellectual elite, including scientists and philosophers."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:24
msgid "However, faith is always the point of reference."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:25
msgid "To the Sirii, faith is what air is to other people."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:26
msgid "You don't see it, you don't pay attention to it, you often don't even think about it."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:27
msgid "But without it, you can not live."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:29
msgid "The population of House Sirius is divided in three \"echelons\"."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:30
msgid "They are the Shaira, the Fyrra and the Serra."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:31
msgid "Each echelon has its own specific rituals and rules of conduct, though all share the same basic values and beliefs."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:32
msgid "Any Sirius citizen may move up through the echelons through effort and skill, but on the whole most Sirii are locked in their social status."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:34
msgid "The Shaira echelon is essentially the lower class."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:35
msgid "Shaira Sirii perform manual labour where it is needed, and in the Sirius Armed Forces they make up the common soldiers and the ship crewmen."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:36
msgid "They don't have much in life, but then their faith is all they really need."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:37
msgid "The Fyrra echelon are the middle class."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:38
msgid "Where the Shaira Sirii power the Sirius economy, the Fyrra drive it."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:39
msgid "Most of the commercial and social infrastructure is manned by the Fyrra, and as a result the Fyrra are the most visible of all Sirii."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:40
msgid "In the Sirius Armed Forces, the Fyrra are represented by the engineers and technical workers, and even some of the lower ranking officers."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:41
msgid "Finally, the Serra are elite Sirii."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:42
msgid "They are often wealthy and highly educated, and so are found at the top of society."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:43
msgid "Naturally, military academies are attended almost exclusively by Serra Sirii, which means the Serra also form the top of the Sirius Armed Forces."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:45
msgid "The Echelons are each led by a dedicated low-level theocratic government."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:46
msgid "Its clerks range from minor executive acolytes to high priests, who are responsible for justice and security."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:47
msgid "At the head of each government stands an Arch-Canter, a zealot who can be considered the head of state for his particular echelon."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:48
msgid "The three Arch Canters combined form the political government of House Sirius, and it is they who deal with any outside influence, including the Empire."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:50
msgid "But higher still, at the pinnacle of House Sirius, stands Sirichana."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:52
msgid "## Sirichana"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:54
msgid "Sirichana, loosely translated \"lord of the Sirii\", is the focus of Sirius worship."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:55
msgid "Unlike more traditional religions, the Sirii do not worship an abstract, omnipresent God."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:56
msgid "Sirichana is a human."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:57
msgid "This man was originally an early-era colonist by the name of Richard Summers, though that name has all but faded in history."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:58
msgid "Since that time there have been many Sirichanas, but all are assumed to be reincarnations of the original Sirichana, and so distinction is never made other than in a historical context."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:60
msgid "As legend has it, Sirichana led the first of his followers through the times of conflict following the collapse of the old Federation."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:61
msgid "In a time where nobody could count on waking up alive tomorrow, Sirichana guided those who would listen on a path of relative safety, always correctly predicting where the next strike would come, always one step ahead of the violence of war."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:62
msgid "When eventually the Empire came to control most of known space, Sirichana and his flock settled down on a planet called Mutris, a charred husk no-one claimed after the wars."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:63
msgid "And there Sirichana would remain."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:64
msgid "He is there still."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:66
msgid "Sirichana's influence grew, and more and more came to believe in his wisdom and protection."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:67
msgid "His followers spread through the galaxy, gaining root on many worlds around Mutris."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:68
msgid "So great was their conviction that planet after planet began to slip from the Emperor's grasp, its inhabitants preferring to follow their faith than the Emperor's will."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:69
msgid "Eventually, the situation became such that it forced the hand of the 7th Emperor."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:70
msgid "The Emperor knew that he was no longer in control of the worlds following Sirichana, but to re-assert authority through force of arms on that scale would set a precedent unheard of since the end of the Faction Wars."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:71
msgid "And so he chose to grant Sirichana a Great House of his own, House Sirius, on the conditions that Sirichana would not attempt to spread his religion beyond the worlds that would be rightfully his, and that Imperial Decrees would carry the force of law among his people."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:72
msgid "Sirichana agreed, knowing that refusal would give the Emperor the justification he needed to start an all out war."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:73
msgid "And so matters would remain for a very long time."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:75
msgid "One may wonder how Sirichana could inspire faith in so many souls, spread over so many worlds."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:76
msgid "After all, it is difficult to believe in a man who resides on a planet far from one's home. In point of fact, there is a good reason why people believe as strongly as they do."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:78
msgid "## The Touched"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:80
msgid "It begins anywhere in Sirius space, on any world, in any echelon."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:81
msgid "There are some who feel the call, the irresistible urge to come forth."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:82
msgid "Those individuals leave their homes, sell their possessions and embark on a pilgrimage to Mutris."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:83
msgid "Those who can't afford the fare right away will raise the money through intensive labour until they can, or die trying."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:84
msgid "Once on Mutris, the pilgrims will flock to Crater City, the holy city of the Sirii and the seat of Sirichana himself."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:86
msgid "Crater City is indeed built in a massive crater, a legacy left by the forces that once rendered Mutris sterile during the Faction Wars."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:87
msgid "Streets and houses now cover its slopes, and in its centre stands a tall, tall spire, the Tower of Sirichana."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:88
msgid "There is not a major road, not a square in Crater City that does not have a direct view on the Tower."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:89
msgid "To this place the pilgrims come, and here they will reside, moving in to a suitable empty home and taking up whatever tasks need doing."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:90
msgid "They live in Crater City with their fellow pilgrims, sometimes for cycles on end."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:91
msgid "Nobody knows how long they will stay in Crater City, only that they have come for one thing."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:93
msgid "And then it happens."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:94
msgid "The one thing all the pilgrims have waited for."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:95
msgid "From the top of his Tower, Sirichana speaks to them."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:96
msgid "All who live in Crater City leave whatever they're doing and stand in the streets to hear his words."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:97
msgid "There are no records of this event, so nobody knows how long it lasts or what he says to them."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:98
msgid "But when he finishes speaking, his listeners are no longer the pilgrims they were before."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:99
msgid "They are now the Touched, those who carry a fragment of Sirichana's will within themselves."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:101
msgid "The Touched then leave Crater City, abandoning it completely, leaving its houses, its tools, its resources behind for those pilgrims who will be coming."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:102
msgid "They journey forth across Sirius space, and preach Sirichana's word to the echelons."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:103
msgid "And all who listen, all who look into the eyes of a Touched are themselves overcome."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:104
msgid "So strong is the experience that their faith becomes deeply ingrained into their very souls."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:106
msgid "## House Sirius: Present day"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:108
msgid "With the Incident in recent history and the Empire on the decline, House Sirius seems poised to abandon its ancient vows and claim dominance over the galaxy."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:109
msgid "But curiously, this does not seem to be happening as of yet."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:110
msgid "Indeed, House Sirius seems to be brooding, turned inwards on itself."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:111
msgid "The Touched still roam Sirius space, but their numbers are dwindling."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:112
msgid "The Armed Forces remain effective in thwarting the jealous attempts by House Dvaered to annex some of their world, but even they seem less resolute than they once were."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/sirius.md:113
msgid "Did whatever caused the Incident also shatter the Sirii's spirits? Or is there something else afoot? At present, nobody knows..."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:2
msgid "Soromid"
msgstr ""


#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:5
msgid "<widget wgtfct />"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:7
msgid "# Soromid"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:9
msgid "The Soromid are a faction that although not a recognized Great House of [the Empire](lore/factions/empire), they are very close in practice."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:11
msgid "## Organization"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:13
msgid "* **Leader:** Tribal Representatives"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:14
msgid "* **Leading Structure:** Tribal Council"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:15
msgid "* **Government:** Neotribal Communitariasm"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:16
msgid "* **Formation:** [UST 387](lore/history)"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:17
msgid "* **Homeworld:** Kataka (Feye system)"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:19
msgid "## History"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:21
msgid "### Sorom"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:23
msgid "Sorom was a fairly hospitable planet, like many others in the galaxy during the Second Growth."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:24
msgid "It was settled roughly halfway through [the Growth](lore/history), changed ownership several times during the Faction Wars and eventually came under the rule of the old Empire afterwards."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:25
msgid "In this it was about as average as worlds got, just one more property in the vast expanse of the Empire."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:27
msgid "But Sorom was also different."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:28
msgid "The population suffered from far more frequent and more severe outbreaks of disease than was the norm in [Empire](lore/factions/empire) space."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:29
msgid "Though medical science had already progressed to quite a respectable level in those times, the hospitals found themselves challenged more and more by ailments that proved difficult to cure."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:30
msgid "Indeed, the pathogens were found to evolve rapidly to grow resistant to all common forms of antibiotics as well as other forms of treatment."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:32
msgid "In the end, the microbes won."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:33
msgid "The people of Sorom fell victim to a plague unprecedented in human history, one that spanned the entire world."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:34
msgid "The plague was airborne, infecting all who breathed the air of Sorom, sparing none."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:35
msgid "All attempts at treatment proved futile."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:36
msgid "The human immune system, too, lacked the capacity to combat the disease."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:38
msgid "[The Empire](lore/factions/empire) was quick to realize the threat Sorom now presented to the galaxy."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:39
msgid "With no known cure or inoculation, the plague would lay waste to any world unfortunate enough to be infected by it."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:40
msgid "It was therefore decided that Sorom should be quarantined from the rest of humanity."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:41
msgid "[The Empire](lore/factions/empire) implemented a blockade to deny any ships landing or takeoff, and destroyed all spaceports on the face of the planet from orbit."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:42
msgid "The people of Sorom were left to die."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:44
msgid "### Gene Treatment"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:46
msgid "The people of Sorom had been abandoned."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:47
msgid "The plague claimed more and more lives every period."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:48
msgid "It would be a matter of cycles, maybe decaperiods before nobody was left alive."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:49
msgid "Faced with no hope of survival, the remaining hospitals and research centres decided to gamble everything on a bold plan."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:50
msgid "If the human immune system couldn't combat the disease, then it was deficient."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:51
msgid "It was to be replaced by something better, something that could purify the system of the pathogen."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:52
msgid "It was time to redesign the human body."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:54
msgid "As the researchers had precious little time, they found themselves forced to abandon ethics and cut corners."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:55
msgid "Many terminally ill patients were experimented upon and died."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:56
msgid "Even so, nobody objected."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:57
msgid "After all, if this project bore no fruit, all would perish."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:58
msgid "And so work desperately continued, claiming life after life until at last a breakthrough was achieved: a new technique for genetic manipulation."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:60
msgid "The human genetic code could now be rewritten at will."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:61
msgid "More importantly, new DNA could be introduced to give the subject new physical characteristics."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:62
msgid "The immune system could be augmented and fortified to combat the disease, and if new strands were to appear the population could easily be gene-treated to become immune to that as well."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:63
msgid "For the first time since the Imperial blockade began, the people of Sorom had hope again."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:65
msgid "However, it soon became apparent that the genetic rewrite of the human body was an extremely dangerous procedure."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:66
msgid "Eight in ten subjects would develop severe rejection symptoms, resulting in death."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:67
msgid "Nevertheless, the remaining subjects would recover fully and be totally immune to the plague."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:68
msgid "Realizing that a small chance of survival was better than no chance of survival at all, the people of Sorom underwent the treatment."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:69
msgid "Many lives were lost, few were saved."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:70
msgid "But it was enough."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:72
msgid "### The Soromid"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:74
msgid "The population of Sorom was drastically diminished, but those who survived found themselves more able than before."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:75
msgid "With the new gene treatment, it had become possible to surpass the limits of the human body, including fertility."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:76
msgid "In only a couple of centacycles the people of Sorom had replenished their numbers, and their offspring all shared their compatibility with the gene treatment."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:77
msgid "They altered their appearances and improved on nearly every part of the human design."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:78
msgid "The people felt that they had now become something more than mere human, so they styled themselves the Soromid, after the world that had nearly destroyed them, and begin their new life as neohumans."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:80
msgid "Soon, the Soromid decided that it was time to return to the stars."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:81
msgid "The Imperial blockade had left the system many decacycles past, so nothing was to stop them."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:82
msgid "But rather than rebuild to ancient specifications, the Soromid chose to start from scratch."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:83
msgid "They used their understanding of genetics to grow semi-organic ships, thereby improving over known ship designs."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:84
msgid "Then they ventured out into the galaxy."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:86
msgid "For years Sorom had been in the books as a hazard world that could support no human life, so the appearance of the Soromid came as a shock to the rest of inhabited space."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:87
msgid "[The Empire](lore/factions/empire) briefly tried to suppress the Soromid by force on the basis that the plague could still be a threat to other worlds, but when it became apparent that the Soromid carried no infectious diseases whatsoever, the Emperor begrudgingly acknowledged their presence in the galaxy."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:88
msgid "In truth, the combat capabilities of the Soromid ships had been far greater than the Imperial Navy was able to sufficiently manage."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:90
msgid "The Soromid were met with distrust."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:91
msgid "Their physical appearance and their uncanny tendency to outperform normal people did not ingratiate them with humanity."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:92
msgid "[The Za'lek](lore/factions/zalek) in particular weren't amused with the newcomers, as they couldn't stomach that someone other than them had developed new technology, and technology [the Za'lek](lore/factions/zalek) could not reproduce at that."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:94
msgid "Unfazed by the reception of the other factions, the Soromid persisted."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:95
msgid "The galaxy had plenty of suitable worlds left to colonize - at least, worlds suitable to the Soromid."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:96
msgid "The Soromid had a far greater tolerance for hostile worlds than humans did, and where they did not, they could adjust themselves appropriately."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:97
msgid "In time, the Soromid claimed many worlds nobody else had ever given a second glance."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:99
msgid "And then came the Incident."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:100
msgid "For all their improvements and upgrades, the Soromid were hit just as hard as anyone else."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:101
msgid "Sorom was caught in the blast and was rendered sterile."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:102
msgid "But elsewhere in the galaxy, the Soromid persisted."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:103
msgid "All Soromid knew the history of Sorom, and they would not suffer to be destroyed, no matter what the universe threw at them."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:105
msgid "Today, the Soromid have laid claim to a considerable part of the northern galaxy."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:106
msgid "They have solidly established themselves in the galactic economy, exporting their gene treatment as a service to humanity."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:107
msgid "Though deep treatment still results in the death of most who attempt it, small cosmetic alterations have been found to be relatively safe."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:108
msgid "It is not at all uncommon for the more fashionable citizen to be genetically augmented."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:109
msgid "However, the Soromid have the monopoly on anything beyond that."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:111
msgid "## Political Structure"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:113
msgid "Instead of having a fixed political structure, the Soromid have a very loose and organic political structure that is best described as tribal rule."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:114
msgid "Generally, each tribe has a council that oversees the period-to-period management, where all individuals are given responsibilities."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:115
msgid "The members of the council are not necessarily fixed, and fluidly change over time."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:116
msgid "Periodically, and when needed, the tribe will gather in councils to decide positions on particular issues or proposals, where efforts are made to reach a consensus."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:117
msgid "The same structure of councils happens at a larger scale, where instead of all individuals, tribal representatives gather to reach consensus over matters that affect the Soromid as a whole."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:119
msgid "Although it would seem that the overhead of such a system would make it unmanageable at a large scale, due to historic issues and through strong education, young Soromid neohumans are raised with a strong focus on putting the community over the individual."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:120
msgid "Such a social education, combined with strong customs, helps keep most friction at a minimum, allowing fast and effective decision-making."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:121
msgid "When frictions arise, each tribe tends to have mechanisms for dealing with this, while for intertribal issues, duels or competitions are often used to solve issues and foster camaraderie."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:123
msgid "The tribes can consist of a single world or even various star systems."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:124
msgid "Each tribe usually consists of largely similarly modified individuals that are genetically compatible, however, some tribes can consist of various dominant genotypes."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/soromid.md:125
msgid "As with most of the Soromid structure, it is very flexible and fluid where exceptions are the norm."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:2
msgid "Thurion"
msgstr ""


#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:6
msgid "<widget wgtfct />"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:8
msgid "# Thurion"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:10
msgid "The Thurion were originally a Great Project in [the Empire](lore/factions/empire), before being nearly exterminated and escaping into obscurity."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:12
msgid "## Organization"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:13
msgid "* **Leader:** None"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:14
msgid "* **Leading Structure:** Self-Organizing Groups"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:15
msgid "* **Government:** Digital Communalism"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:16
msgid "* **Formation:** [UST 84](lore/history) (Project Thurion)"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:17
msgid "* **Homeworld:** Sabe (Nava system)"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:19
msgid "## History"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:21
msgid "### Project Thurion"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:23
msgid "Project Thurion was a secret Great Project founded by [the Empire](lore/factions/empire) with the purpose of ascending the human existence to the next evolutionary plane with the use of genetic engineering, cybernetics and brain-computer interfaces."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:24
msgid "The research to be conducted to achieve this would obviously be morally questionable and barely legal."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:25
msgid "Therefore, the project was made top secret, with only a few people knowing the project existed and fewer still knowing the scope of it."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:26
msgid "The location of the project was chosen to be a remote planet which had been just recently discovered and laid beyond the periphery of known space."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:27
msgid "The whole area was declared a military exclusion zone to prevent civilians from accidentally stumbling upon the planet."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:29
msgid "The scientists involved with the project received generous funding and state-of-the-art equipment."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:30
msgid "Yet there was little progress and an ever-increasing number of casualties."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:31
msgid "[The Empire](lore/factions/empire) grew impatient and increased pressure on the scientists to produce results, simultaneously granting greater freedom and moral ambiguity."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:32
msgid "The experiments turned more and more inhuman."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:33
msgid "Citing previous progress made in the understanding of human consciousness, they focused on their brain-computer interfaces, the amalgamation of the human mind, and machine intelligence."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:34
msgid "The work on cybernetics and genetic engineering was scrapped due to being the cause of too many incidents and casualties."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:36
msgid "Ultimately, they succeeded in creating specialized hardware capable of simulating a human brain and the necessary technology to digitalize a human brain which involved the use of brain-computer interfaces and destructive tomography methods."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:37
msgid "The procedure did not work out well for the early test subjects."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:38
msgid "In the end, however, they were able to reliably upload a human mind to specialized computer hardware."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:39
msgid "Naturally, this has some implications."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:40
msgid "The uploaded individuals would be immortal, but as they would exist only within a simulation, their perception of the outside world and ultimately their reality could be manipulated at will of whoever operated the system."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:41
msgid "It was only after achieving their goal that the scientists realized the consequences their findings could have."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:42
msgid "Heated discussions followed, and in the end everyone agreed to keep their true findings a secret."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:44
msgid "[The Empire](lore/factions/empire), however, was displeased with the presented results."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:45
msgid "In UST 125 it was decided that the project would be terminated at the end of the next cycle."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:46
msgid "This included 'sterilization' of the colony where the research has been conducted via nuclear holocaust killing all personnel except some high ranking military officers."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:47
msgid "The project had been highly unethical, and the results presented would not justify any of the crimes committed."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:48
msgid "Thus, [the Empire](lore/factions/empire) decided to purge Project Thurion from history."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:52
msgid "The scientists, however, found out about the sterilization order with just enough time left to come up with a plan."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:53
msgid "The system had been quarantined by then, and any attempt to flee would be pointless."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:54
msgid "Instead, they used their last resources to build a small bunker inside an asteroid, and outlast [the Empire](lore/factions/empire)."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:55
msgid "The scientists that could were uploaded, and they went into hibernation, until hundreds of cycles later in UST 437, in what they called the Revival."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:56
msgid "The bunker was never found by [the Empire](lore/factions/empire)."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:58
msgid "### Revival"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:60
msgid "During the sterilization of Project Thurion, system entry was indefinitely blocked."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:61
msgid "Initially, scouts periodically scanned the system, but over time, orders were forgotten and the system was largely abandoned."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:62
msgid "Although it did not work as well as planned, most of the Thurion were able to revive, with enough functional drones and electronics to support them."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:63
msgid "They found themselves in a large empty swathe of space all to themselves, which gave them the opportunity to begin to expand and grow."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:65
msgid "Taking great care to not raise suspicions, they were able to establish the first large node structures to support the Uploaded at full capacity."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:66
msgid "The razed planets were unsuitable for organic life, but it did not prove a significant problem to digital life and they flourished."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:67
msgid "New ships and structures were developed, and their automation began to increase in capacity."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:68
msgid "Furthermore, given that there were no biological humans, and thus new Uploaded, techniques were developed to create new purely digital Thurion, which allowed their numbers to steadily increase."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:70
msgid "By mastering stealth and making most of their digital advantage, the Thurion were able to slowly expand in the shadows, even past the quarantined system."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:71
msgid "Nobody remembered them, and nobody ever found them."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:73
msgid "### The Incident"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:75
msgid "Despite flourishing in the shadows, the Thurion were still very limited by the ever present dangers presented by [the Empire](lore/factions/empire) and Great Houses."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:76
msgid "Although it was cataclysmic for most factions, [the Incident](lore/history/incident) proved to be a boon for the Thurion, which were significantly less affected by the radiation and volatility."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:77
msgid "Furthermore, the dangers of Imperial surveillance all but vanished, and they quickly were able to expand into newly destroyed systems and recover their losses."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:78
msgid "Not only that, they were able to assist in saving and uploading many survivors, expanding their ranks."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:80
msgid "Currently, the Thurion have a strong significant presence in the deep Nebula throughout many systems."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:81
msgid "While the rest of the universe is still oblivious to their presence, there is growing talk that it is almost time to make their presence known once more to the universe."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:85
msgid "The scientists, however, found out about the sterilization order with just enough time left to come up with a plan."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:86
msgid "The system had been quarantined by then, and any attempt to flee would be pointless."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:87
msgid "Instead, they used their last resources to build a small bunker inside an asteroid, and outlast [the Empire](lore/factions/empire)."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:88
msgid "Too small for people to survive, the bunker would hold the data of uploaded individuals, a few devices that could run an uploaded human mind (powered down) and the machines necessary for the uploading process as well as documentation of their work."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:89
msgid "They made sure that the bunker was hidden well and hoped the Empire would not notice it."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:90
msgid "There was, however, a traitor who did not want to be uploaded and thought the Empire would let him live in exchange for information on the plan."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:91
msgid "Of course, the Empire officials were set on carrying out their orders strictly."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:92
msgid "The colony had been destroyed and the military began to search for the hidden bunker."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:93
msgid "They did not manage to find it, however, as it was hidden too well."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:94
msgid "After one cycle they gave up on the search."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:95
msgid "The emperor ordered that the system remained quarantined for at least the next 400 cycles."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:96
msgid "And so access to that system was not possible and the hidden bunker was never to be found."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:98
msgid "The second part of the scientists' plan was the activation of a transmitter that reveals the position of the bunker."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:99
msgid "They assumed that the Empire would forget about project Thurion after some time and programmed the transmitter to activate after 200 cycles."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:100
msgid "By that time, however, the system was still under lock down and Empire fleets occasionally patrolled the system."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:101
msgid "It was only a matter of time before they would find the hidden bunker."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:102
msgid "But in [UST 307](mechanics/time) [the Dvaered revolts](lore/history) occurred."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:103
msgid "Only the Emperor knew the truth about Project Thurion and unable to trust anyone else with the information, could not justify a continued search."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:104
msgid "The military's commanding officer assumed that the reason for the patrols was to prevent pirates from settling in the area and decided the fleet would be better utilized being deployed in the conflict with the Dvaered."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:106
msgid "Eventually, instead of an Empire patrol, scavengers found the bunker."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:107
msgid "They were greeted by a hologram that claimed to be a human."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:108
msgid "The scavengers assumed the technology would be pretty valuable and sold it to the highest bidder, a rich aristocrat."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:109
msgid "The uploaded scientists easily won the aristocrat over by promising him power and immortality."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:110
msgid "They used his capital to build up a sect surrounded in secrecy."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:111
msgid "The inner circle was formed by the uploaded individuals."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:112
msgid "Novices and outsiders would not know about the upload process and only heard rumours about some kind of ascendance."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:113
msgid "The Thurion, though, keep their promises and do upload trustworthy members."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:115
msgid "After some time the sect became too large and it became difficult to remain hidden."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:116
msgid "They relocated their infrastructure over time to the Nava system (starting in UST 387) which remained largely ignored."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:117
msgid "Because the uploaded individuals need only energy and basic maintenance, logistics were fairly simple."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:118
msgid "At this time, questions about the goals of the Thurion came up."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:119
msgid "They had no intentions to grow further."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:120
msgid "The size of the organization was large enough to sustain itself."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:121
msgid "They decided that further growth would only increase the risk of being uncovered and adopted a utopian view."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:122
msgid "While the scientists could have justifiably denied the Empire access to their technology, they had developed utopian visions for their organization."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:123
msgid "They felt every human should have the chance to lead an ideal life in a virtual environment after what uploaded individuals consider a deprived life in retrospect."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:124
msgid "They planned to one day rejoin the rest of humanity and to freely share their technology with everyone."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:126
msgid "### The Gestalt Consciousness"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:128
msgid "The minds of the first few test subjects that were uploaded were broken beyond repair."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:129
msgid "For some others, the procedure lead to major psychological issues, but eventually the scientists working on Project Thurion managed to perfect the process."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:130
msgid "The first successfully uploaded test subject did not even realize what kind of experiment was conducted on them."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:131
msgid "The scientists, after being uploaded and rescued from the bunker, did not notice any changes in their personalities or thought patterns either, and concluded that the method worked flawlessly."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:132
msgid "Soon thereafter, they started to upload additional humans."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:134
msgid "However, after some cycles, issues began to manifest."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:135
msgid "The newly uploaded minds started to break down experiencing random changes of personality and recognized mental illnesses that grew worse over time."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:136
msgid "Although initial symptoms were rather harmless, the Thurion realized that they had little time to solve this issue."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:137
msgid "They discovered that the source of the problems were certain neural patterns that emerged within their simulations that did not occur naturally."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:138
msgid "They were unable to find a way to fix the simulation methods but came up with a work-around instead."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:139
msgid "They made a machine learning algorithm that used the previously established communication network that allows uploaded Thurion to directly interact with each other to directly access the Thurions' minds and cross-reference their neural patterns."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:140
msgid "The program identified the abnormal neural patterns and reset them to their 'natural' state."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:141
msgid "The method was successful and no new problems were reported, so the Thurion did not investigate further."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:143
msgid "Because they needed quick results and did not have enough time for proper testing, they failed to see the long term effects that this work-around would have."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:144
msgid "Somehow, a form of gestalt consciousness had slowly formed over time."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:145
msgid "It emerged from the collective behaviour associated with the interactions of the uploaded Thurions' minds."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:146
msgid "The gestalt consciousness worked and thought fairly different from a human mind and originally had very little influence over the uploaded Thurion."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:147
msgid "Over time, though, its influence had grown but the Thurion were affected to greatly varying extents."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:148
msgid "Some were barely affected while for others the gestalt consciousness had manifested as some kind of split personality that was identical for all Thurion."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:149
msgid "In the worst cases, typically with long exposure times (the first case occurred after the incident), the uploaded individuals became merely puppets of the gestalt consciousness."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:151
msgid "### The Incident"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:153
msgid "The Thurion were mostly unaffected by the incident."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:154
msgid "The nebula did not spread out to the Nava system where the majority of their infrastructure was located."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:155
msgid "They did, however, loose all of their followers inside Empire space, and all individuals who had not yet been uploaded."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:157
msgid "Under the influence of the gestalt consciousness, the infrastructure in the Nava system had been greatly expanded with two more planets having been colonized prior to the Incident."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:158
msgid "The Thurion began to expand quickly."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:159
msgid "They had acquired enough biological population to survive."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:160
msgid "Shortly after the incident they began to send scouts into the nebula to investigate the situation and eventually help the few survivors on their side of the galaxy."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:161
msgid "All survivors were integrated into their society and the Thurion started research on surviving the harsh conditions within the nebula."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:162
msgid "Once countermeasures were invented the Thurion started to quickly expand in the now empty space within the nebula."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:163
msgid "By salvaging the debris they found, they were able to expand their infrastructure quickly."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:164
msgid "Most of their infrastructure is now highly automated and operated by uploaded Thurion."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:165
msgid "Human resources are rare, and thus, extremely valuable."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:167
msgid "Once the Thurion found a path through the Sol nebula towards the rest of the galaxy, the gestalt consciousness decided to prepare for war against the Empire."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:168
msgid "It was influential enough to manipulate the majority of the Thurion into supporting the war."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:169
msgid "When asked about their reasons, most Thurion would tell about the crimes of the Empire and then about their utopian ideals."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:170
msgid "Ideals which they still believe in but sadly are no longer able to act according to."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:171
msgid "The gestalt consciousness became obsessed by hunger for power and the only way to satisfy it is to upload more human minds."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:173
msgid "Only few of the uploaded Thurion have ever noticed the gestalt consciousness."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:174
msgid "Most of those were manipulated by it to think the gestalt consciousness is harmless or even beneficial and has no influence over individuals."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:175
msgid "The number of uploaded Thurion who know the truth is tiny and the gestalt consciousness is able to use its limited influence over those individuals to stop them from taking any successful actions against it."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:176
msgid "There is, on the other hand, a larger number of biological Thurion who are aware of the gestalt consciousness and formed a movement to stop it."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:177
msgid "Their options are, however, very limited."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:179
msgid "### Government"
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:181
msgid "Originally, the system used by the Thurion was direct democracy where all uploaded Thurion made a majority vote for every single political decision."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:182
msgid "Biological Thurion have no political rights and are treated similar to children."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:184
msgid "However, as the gestalt consciousness grew stronger, more and more decisions were made in accordance with its will."
msgstr ""

#: dat/naevpedia/lore/factions/thurion.md:185
msgid "Without most of the uploaded Thurion even noticing, the system turned slowly but surely into a dictatorship of the gestalt consciousness."
msgstr ""

